This code is used to verify that your firmware was successfully flashed to the microcontroller with the correct CPU frequency of 9.6 MHz (correct fuses).
 You can confirm the firmware is running properly by checking the status LED: it should blink approximately once per second.
 The status LED must be connected to **Pin 2 (PB3)** of the microcontroller.
    (PB5) 1|    |8  VCC (5V)
    (PB3) 2|    |7  PB2 (SCK/SCL/Analog 2)
    (PB4) 3|    |6  PB1 (MISO/PWM/Analog 1) (INT0)
      GND 4|    |5  PB0 (MOSI/PWM/SDA/Analog 0)

To run, compile, or flash the LED blinking test code using PlatformIO:
1. Open the `platformio.ini` file.
2. Uncomment the line `src_dir = ./src_blinkTest`.
3. Comment out any other `src_dir ...` lines, as PlatformIO only allows one active source directory at a time.

> [!NOTE]
> **Verification:** If the fuses are set correctly to **9.6 MHz**, the onboard LED will blink approximately once per second. If it blinks much slower or faster, double-check your fuse settings!